lived_experience_narrative: I struggled with anxiety and panic attacks throughout my teenage years, which made school and socializing difficult. Art therapy and mindfulness helped me regain control of my emotions, and I want to share these tools with others.

During college, I faced severe depression that left me feeling isolated. Staying active through sports and practicing meditation helped me find balance. I want to help others discover the power of movement and mindfulness.

After experiencing trauma as a teenager, I found healing through music and writing. Yoga also became a safe space for me to reconnect with myself. I'm here to support others on their journey to recovery.
Growing up with ADHD was challenging because I often felt misunderstood. Gaming and coding became my outlets for creativity and focus. I want to help others embrace their unique strengths.

Recovering from an eating disorder taught me the importance of self-compassion and finding joy in simple things like cooking and gardening. I want to support others in finding their path to self-love.

Living with Bipolar Disorder has been a journey of ups and downs. Writing poetry and spending time in nature have been grounding for me. I'm passionate about helping others navigate their own mental health journeys.
OCD once controlled my life, but therapy and yoga helped me reclaim it. Volunteering has also given me purpose and joy. I hope to inspire others to find their own sources of strength.
